Common transport (MHD) in Prague will introduce the bullet in their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of Pražský Dopragrní podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will get into the metro, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible to almost one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard card.
Passengers can buy a coupon for 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both have it recorded on their cards at the information points and offices of the Doprahrní Podnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nadraží Holeshovice, Andel, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy online coupons on the Dopravní vdnik websites: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people took advantage of the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can permanently forget the tickets in the metro stations, where they had to so far become impatient in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will purchase their coupon online and will be registered on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is the availability of passengers with a trained staff, which will help those interested in purchasing via the Internet and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said the spokesperson of the Martin Opatrny project.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, reminding the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, it should have twenty-four," Opatrny added.
An auto will control the coupon instead of the driver
