"The vicious circle of poverty, segregation and unemployment must be broken; the opportunities provided by democracy must be given to Roma children, so that they can participate as citizens of the right to the future of Europe" - Járóka demanded.
On behalf of the European Year for Equal Opportunities, which is ensured for all, the objective of the European Summit on Equal Opportunities organised each year since the Berlin Summit last year is to provide a unique platform to support measures taken to promote equal opportunities and to combat discrimination at European and national level.
